There are two famous waterfalls in South America.
One is the widest and the other is the highest in the world.
Iguazu Falls is the widest waterfall.
Is is between Brazil and Argentina.
It is about 2,700 meters wide.
You can go under the falls in a boat.
Angle Falls is the highest waterfall.
It is in Venezuela.
It is almost 1,000 meters high.
It is much higher than Tokyo Skytree.
What is the widest waterfall in the world?
